{{no footnotes|date=October 2009}}
'''Heath forest''' is a type of [[tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests|tropical moist forest]] found in areas with acidic, sandy soils that are extremely nutrient-poor. Notable examples are the [[Rio Negro campinarana]] of the [[Amazon Basin]] in [[South America]], and the [[Sundaland heath forests]] (also known as ''Kerangas'' forests) of [[Borneo]] and neighboring islands.

