{{Refimprove|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox rockunit | name = Ukureyskaya Formation | image = | caption = | type = [[Geological formation]] | age = {{fossilrange|169|144|latest=144|[[Bajocian]]&ndash;[[Tithonian]], 169&ndash;144 Ma}} | period = Jurassic | prilithology = [[Sandstone]], [[siltstone]], [[tuffite]] | otherlithology = [[Mudstone]] | namedfor = | namedby = | region = | country = {{RUS}} | coordinates = | unitof = | subunits = Lower, Middle and Upper subformations | underlies = [[Utanskaya Formation]] | overlies = [[Kulindinskaya Formation]] | thickness = Several hundred metres | extent = [[Zabaykalsky Krai]] | area = | map = | map_caption = }}
The '''Ukureyskaya Formation''' is a geological formation made up of [[Middle Jurassic]] and [[Late Jurassic]] layers.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sinitsa|first=S.|last2=Reshetova|first2=S.|last3=Vilmova|first3=E.|date=2017|title=Hypostratotypes of Ukureyskaya Formation of Novoberezovka and Olov Depressions of Transbaikalia (Part 1. Hypostratotype-1 of Ukureyskaya Formation of Novoberezovka Depression)|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/321188437_Hypostratotypes_of_Ukureyskaya_Formation_of_Novoberezovka_and_Olov_Depressions_of_Transbaikalia_Part_1_Hypostratotype-1_of_Ukureyskaya_Formation_of_Novoberezovka_Depression|journal=Transbaikal State University Journal|volume=23|issue=6|pages=52–62|doi=10.21209/2227-9245-2017-23-6-52-62|issn=2227-9245}}</ref> It covers large areas around Kulinda. The formation is where the [[Type (biology)|type specimen]] fossils of ''[[Kulindadromeus zabaikalicus]]'' were found, alongside a single tooth from a medium-sized [[Theropoda|theropod]] of unknown affiliations and other indeterminate [[Ornithischia|ornithschians]].<ref>"[http://palaeo.gly.bris.ac.uk/melanosomes/Kulindafind.html The Kulinda fossil site]", University of Bristol Palaeobiology Research Group. Retrieved 4 April 2015</ref>
